Male genitalia (
Fig. 49
). Uncus narrowed from base to basal 3/4, distal 1/4 slender, pointed at apex. Gnathos wide at base, narrowed to apex, with a small pointed process apically. Tegumen with height 1.5 times length of uncus. Valva almost uniformly broad before cucullus; cucullus sub-rectangular, length twice of maximum width, uniformly wide to obtuse apex; inner process spine-shaped; costa convex triangularly; sacculus 7/10 length of valva, nearly straight on ventral margin, apex rounded, free from valva, exceeding ventral corner of cucullus. Vinculum narrowly banded; saccus rounded anteriorly. Juxta oval; anellar lobes conical, about same length as juxta, with short setae. Aedeagus 1.3 times length of valva, with a sclerite at basal 1/4, with numerous spicules ranging from basal 2/5 to 4/5; basal 2/3 almost uniform in width, distal 1/3 gradually narrowed; distal process clubbed, 1/3 length of aedeagus.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 69
). Intersegmental membrane between papillae anales and eighth abdominal segment twice length of papillae anales. Apophyses posteriores 1.5 times length of apophyses anteriores. Eighth segment straight on posterior margin, with long setae; eighth tergite straight on anterior margin; eighth sternite triangularly produced anteriorly. Antrum sub-rectangular, slightly concave on posterior margin, concave in wide V-shape on an- terior margin. Ductus bursae almost uniform, 2/3 length of corpus bursae. Corpus bursae elliptical; signum located close to posterior margin, crescent in shape, length half of median width of corpus bursae, with a sclerotized ridge, with sparse microspines in surrounding area. Appendix bursae originating from transition of ductus bursae and corpus bursae; bulla rounded, at distal 1/4; ductus seminalis with dense granules distally.
